{"title_page": "Shukrullo", "text_new": "'''Shukrulla''' (also found as '''Shukrullo'''; born September 2, 1921<ref>''The Modern Uzbeks: From the Fourteenth Century to the Present: a Cultural History'', Edward Allworth\n1990, {{ISBN|0-8179-8732-0}}. p. 323</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Shukrullo (1921)|url=http://www.ziyouz.uz/en/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=114:shukrullo-1921&catid=41:literature-of-30-80s-of-xx-century&Itemid=53|publisher=ziyouz.uz|accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref>) is a noted [[Uzbek language]] poet.  He has been honored with [[Uzbekistan]]'s Hamza Award and the title of Uzbekistan People's Poet.<ref>http://www.drunkenboat.com/db10/01asi/shukrulla.html</ref>  His poetry has been translated into many languages, and has appeared in magazines<ref>[[World Literature Today]], v.70, 1996 [https://www.questia.com/googleScholar.qst?docId=96619821]</ref> and anthologies.<ref>[http://www.cse.iitk.ac.in/~amit/books/chang-2008-language-for-new.html Language for a New Century] p.45</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Uzbekistani male poets]]\n[[Category:1921 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{Uzbekistan-poet-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Shukrulla''' (also found as '''Shukrullo'''; born September 2, 1921<ref>''The Modern Uzbeks: From the Fourteenth Century to the Present: a Cultural History'', Edward Allworth\n1990, {{ISBN|0-8179-8732-0}}. p. 323</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Shukrullo (1921)|url=http://www.ziyouz.uz/en/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=114:shukrullo-1921&catid=41:literature-of-30-80s-of-xx-century&Itemid=53|publisher=ziyouz.uz|accessdate=4 November 2013}}</ref>) is a noted [[Uzbek language]] poet.  He has been honored with [[Uzbekistan]]'s Hamza Award and the title of Uzbekistan People's Poet.<ref>http://www.drunkenboat.com/db10/01asi/shukrulla.html</ref>  His poetry has been translated into many languages, and has appeared in magazines<ref>[[World Literature Today]], v.70, 1996 [https://www.questia.com/googleScholar.qst?docId=96619821]</ref> and anthologies.<ref>[http://www.cse.iitk.ac.in/~amit/books/chang-2008-language-for-new.html Language for a New Century] p.45</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Uzbekistani male poets]]\n[[Category:1921 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n\n{{Uzbekistan-poet-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shukrullo"}
{"title_page": "Henryk Sawistowski", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}\n'''Henryk Sawistowski''' was born in 1925 in [[Grudzi\u0105dz]], [[Poland]].\n\nSawistowski started his education in Grudzi\u0105dz, during World War II while in military service. After the war he moved to London, England.\n\nIn 1974, after earning a diploma he became a lecturer at his school - the [[Imperial College London]] gradually rising the ranks to vice-president of [[Institution of Chemical Engineers]] in 1981 and dean of [[City and Guilds]] college until his death in 1984.\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sawistowski, Henryk}}\n[[Category:1925 births]]\n[[Category:1984 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Grudzi\u0105dz]]\n[[Category:Polish academics]]\n[[Category:Deans of the City and Guilds College]]\n\n\n{{Poland-bio-stub}}\n{{ImperialCollege-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}\n'''Henryk Sawistowski''' was born in 1925 in [[Grudzi\u0105dz]], [[Poland]].\n\nSawistowski started his education in Grudzi\u0105dz, during World War II while in military service. After the war he moved to London, England.\n\nIn 1974, after earning a diploma he became a lecturer at his school - the [[Imperial College London]] gradually rising the ranks to vice-president of [[Institution of Chemical Engineers]] in 1981 and dean of [[City and Guilds]] college until his death in 1984.\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sawistowski, Henryk}}\n[[Category:1925 births]]\n[[Category:1984 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Grudzi\u0105dz]]\n[[Category:Polish academics]]\n\n\n{{Poland-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Shadowssettle", "label": "safe", "comment": "+Deans of the C&GC; as an administrator classifies as a uni stub (see similarOxon stubsCantab stubs)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henryk_Sawistowski"}
